item.text:
Code
  • set of instructions executed by a computer
  • set of conventions used to communicate meaning
  • system of rules to convert information
  • a type of legislation intended to compile all, or a significant amount of laws in a particular area

Law
  • system of rules that are enforced through social institutions to govern behaviour
  • a binding custom or practice of a community
  • a rule or mode of conduct or action that is prescribed or formally recognised as binding by a supreme controlling authority or is made obligatory by a sanction
